```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing events to one per subscription/month (keep latest by event_id)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_subscriptions_with_plan.sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with plan tier (handle missing plans)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        sub.subscription_id,
        sub.user_id,
        sub.started_at,
        sub.ended_at,
        sub.status,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(p.monthly_price, 0) AS monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} sub
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = sub.plan_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/mart/fct_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics: active count, MRR, unique users by tier and industry
WITH subscription_events AS (
    SELECT
        DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month)::DATE AS month,
        sub.subscription_id,
        sub.user_id,
        sub.tier,
        uc.industry,
        be.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_with_plan') }} sub
        ON sub.subscription_id = be.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_users_with_company') }} uc
        ON uc.user_id = sub.user_id
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM subscription_events
GROUP BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
